          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>Several first-party PlayStation games have found their way to PC over the past few years, and now’s your chance to pick them up for cheap. A handful of <a href="https://www.amazon.com/stores/page/preview?isSlp=1&amp;isPreview=1&amp;asins=B0CBNN7BP1,B0CZPM4KLZ,B0CBNQPBCY,B0CLYZD4X2,B0CLYZ1FCP,B0CBNPMX7P&amp;tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">PlayStation Studios PC games are discounted at Amazon</a> ahead of the holidays,<strong> all of which are offered as digital Steam keys</strong>--making this a great time to pile a few more games into your ever-growing Steam library. The only caveat? Most of these deals are exclusive to <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/prime/pipeline/signup?tag=gamespot-promos-20&amp;tag=gamespot-buybutton-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Amazon Prime</a> members. Consider signing up to cash in on the deals, however, as you’ll also gain access to free shipping, the impressive Prime Video catalog, monthly free games via Prime gaming, and tons of other benefits.</p><p>The best deals in the bunch include <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CBNN7BP1?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Sackboy: A Big Adventure</a> for $12.59 (was $60), <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CBNN7BP1?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Ratchet &amp; Clank: Rift Apart</a> for $27 (was $60), and <a href="https://www.amazon.com/God-War-Standard-Online-Game/dp/B0CBNQPBCY?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">God of War</a> (2018) for just $20 (was $50). If you pick up God of War (or have already played it on PS4 or PS5), the Steam version of the sequel <a href="https://www.amazon.com/God-War-Ragnar%C3%B6k-Standard-Online/dp/B0D8M459CW?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">God of War: Ragnarok</a> is also available on Amazon, and while it's not on sale, it's worth adding to your shopping cart if you want to continue Kratos and Atreus’ journey.</p><p>One of the newest games on sale is <a href="https://www.amazon.com/HELLDIVERS-Standard-Online-Game-Code/dp/B0CLYZ1FCP?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Helldivers 2</a>, as you’ll find it for just $32 (was $40). The popular cooperative shooter tasks you and three friends with repelling aliens, robots, and other evil creatures from inching their way toward Super Earth. Its player count isn’t anywhere near its all-time high from earlier this year, but you’ll regularly find around 20,000 others online--making it easy to find a crew for your next mission. For a jumpstart, consider springing for the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/HELLDIVERS-Standard-Online-Game-Code/dp/B0CLYZD4X2?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Super Citizen Edition</a> that’s on sale for $48 (was $60). Along with the base game, you’ll get various cosmetics, such as an armor set and cape, plus a premium Warbond with additional unlockables.</p><p>You'll find a list of all the discounted PlayStation Studios PC releases listed below. It's worth noting that <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CBNN7BP1?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Ratchet &amp; Clank: Rift Apart's</a> discount is the only price cut that is available to all shoppers; the rest require an Amazon Prime account to access the deals. However, you can sign up for the service and get immediate access to all the discounts.</p><h2>PlayStation Studios PC Game Deals at Amazon</h2><ul><li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Ghost-Tsushima-DIRECTORS-CUT-Online/dp/B0CZPM4KLZ?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Ghost of Tsushima: Director's Cut (Steam)</a> -- $48 ($<del>60</del>)</li><li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/God-War-Standard-Online-Game/dp/B0CBNQPBCY?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">God of War (Steam)</a> -- $20 ($<del>50</del>)</li><li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/HELLDIVERS-Standard-Online-Game-Code/dp/B0CLYZD4X2?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Helldivers 2: Super Citizen Edition (Steam)</a> -- $48 ($<del>60</del>)</li><li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/HELLDIVERS-Standard-Online-Game-Code/dp/B0CLYZ1FCP?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Helldivers 2: Standard Edition (Steam)</a> -- $32 ($<del>40</del>)</li><li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CBNN7BP1?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Ratchet &amp; Clank: Rift Apart (Steam)</a> -- $27 ($<del>60</del>)</li><li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CBNPMX7P?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Sackboy: A Big Adventure (Steam)</a> -- $12.59 ($<del>60</del>)</li></ul><hr><p>While it's not required, a DualSense controller is highly recommended for playing PlayStation Studios games on PC. Not only were all these games designed with that controller's button layout in mind, but the PC ports also support all the cool DualSense features you normally only get to experience on PS5, including adaptive triggers and haptic feedback. Luckily, you can snag a long list of DualSense colors at big discounts, including the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/PlayStation-DualSenseTM-Wireless-Controller-Gaming-Console/dp/B0CQKLS4RP?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">standard white model</a> for $54 (was $75) or flashier options like the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/PlayStation-DualSenseTM-Wireless-Controller-Gaming-Console/dp/B0CJTCQRNL?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Sterling Silver edition</a> for $59 (was $80). You'll find a full list of all the discounted DualSense controllers below--just note that while both Amazon and Walmart offer these deals, availability may differ between retailers, so be sure to check all the links below to see what's in stock.</p><h2>PS5 DualSense Controller Deals at Amazon and Walmart</h2><ul><li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/PlayStation-DualSenseTM-Wireless-Controller-Gaming-Console/dp/B0CQKLS4RP?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">White at Amazon</a> -- $54 (<del>$75</del>) <strong>|</strong> Also at <a href="https://clicks.trx-hub.com/xid/fandom_32094_gamespot?q=https%3A%2F%2Fgoto.walmart.com%2Fc%2F1804712%2F565706%2F9383%3Fveh%3Daff%26sourceid%3Dimp_000011112222333344%26u%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FSony-PS5-DualSense-Wireless-Controller-White%2F5226693883%26subId1%3Dsubid_value&amp;p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Farticles%2Fplaystation-studios-pc-games-are-steeply-discounted-for-amazon-prime-members%2F1100-6528345%2F&amp;event_type=click" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Walmart</a></li><li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/PlayStation-DualSenseTM-Wireless-Controller-Gaming-Console/dp/B0CQKKHT5J?tag=gamespot-promos-20" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Midnight Black at Amazon</a> -- $54 (<del>$75</del>) <strong>|</strong> Also at <a href="https://clicks.trx-hub.com/xid/fandom_32094_gamespot?q=https%3A%2F%2Fgoto.walmart.com%2Fc%2F1804712%2F565706%2F9383%3Fveh%3Daff%26sourceid%3Dimp_000011112222333344%26u%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FSony-PS5-DualSense-Wireless-Controller-Midnight-Black%2F5226693884%26subId1%3Dsubid_value&amp;p=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Farticles%2Fplaystation-studios-pc-games-are-steeply-discounted-for-amazon-prime-members%2F1100-6528345%2F&amp;event_type=click" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Walmart</a></li><li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Pla